{"id": 232067764, "title": "LG Election 2024: ADC Leaders Brainstorm With Party's Candidates In Delta", "text": "The leaders of African Democratic Congress (ADC) have enjoined the party\u2019s candidates in the forthcoming July 2024 local government election to work-hard for victory, adding that the election would serve as a \u201clitmus test\u201d for Governor Oborevwori\u2019s political integrity. The leadership, therefore, called on Delta State Independent Electoral Commission (DSIEC) to be neutral and allow the will of the people to prevail. Daily Independent learnt this at weekend as the National and State Leaders of African Democratic Congress (ADC) met with its candidates at the State party Secretariat in Asaba, Delta State capital Delta as ADC party leaders brainstormed on way-forward towards securing victory for the party come next month, July 2024 local government election in Delta State. The party leaders had assured its candidates in the forthcoming Local Government election in Delta of the party\u2019s support which is a follow up of the election activities to ensure that the will of the people, that is the electorates prevail during the forthcoming July election in Delta State. Those party leaders present at the meeting with ADC party candidates for the forthcoming Local Government election in Delta State included, amongst others: ADC Delta State Chairman, Engr Okolie C Austine, former presidential aspirant and national leader of the party HE Dr Chukwuka Monye, former ADC Delta North Senatorial Candidate of the party and current ADC Deputy National Chairman, Hon Chief Dr Kenneth Chibogwu Gbandi. Others are: ADC Delta State Secretary, Hon Chief Yebi Ebu Napoleon Ck, ADC Administrative Secretary, Mr Nwabuzo Nonso, and most importantly the ADC Candidates for the forthcoming Local Government Area Election in Delta which included amongst others are: Mr Okpah Steven Okolie, Mr Abia Okamadu, Comrade Randy Ugbejie and the host of others. Speaking at the during the brainstorming sessions, Dr Chukwuka Monye charged the candidates to go back to their various communities, political wards and polling units and return victory to the party. \u201cHe said: \u201cThe only genuine, renewed hope in Delta State is now ADC. Also, we call on the Delta State Independent Electoral Commission (DSIEC) on the need to remain neutral and allow the will of the people to prevail. \u201cAnything short of that will not be tolerated. We also, Charged the candidates to work for their victories by ensuring that they win the election. \u201cEvery candidates of ADC should not be intimidated of electoral manipulation rather they should work hard to win the election at the polling units for everyone to see they won and leave the rest\u201d. ADC Deputy National Chairman & Party\u2019s Former 2023 Delta North Senatorial Candidate, Hon. Chief Dr. Kenneth Gbandi, has assured the candidates of the both ADC State & National party leaders maximum support as he Charged candidates on the need to double their efforts towards reaching out to the electorates in their various localities. He said: \u201cThe only deciding factor in the election is the electorates. We call on Governor Sheriff Oborevwori to play his fatherly role as the father of the State in ensuring that free, fair and Credible LGA Election is guaranteed as all eyes are now on him as a litmus test\u201d. Finally, ADC Delta State Chairman, Engr Okolie Chukwuekwu Austine, who doubles as the Delta State Treasurer, Inter-party Advisory Council (IPAC), has also assured the candidates that their victory will be secured. \u201cThe only thing we expect from the candidates is to win the election and that is all\u201d.", "summary": "<div style=\"margin-bottom:20px;\"><img width=\"1600\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240608-WA0032.jpg\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"high\" srcset=\"https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240608-WA0032.jpg 1600w, https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240608-WA0032-300x225.jpg 300w, https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240608-WA0032-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240608-WA0032-768x576.jpg 768w, https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240608-WA0032-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240608-WA0032-86x64.jpg 86w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" /></div>The leaders of African Democratic Congress (ADC) have enjoined the party&#8217;s candidates in the forthcoming July 2024 local government election to work-hard for victory, adding that the election would serve as a &#8220;litmus test&#8221; ", "url": "https://independent.ng/lg-election-2024-adc-leaders-brainstorm-with-partys-candidates-in-delta/", "image": "https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240608-WA0032.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 16:20:29", "author": "Victor Bieni", "authors": ["Victor Bieni"], "language": "en", "catgory": "politics", "source_country": "ng", "sentiment": 0.271}